1) API stands for Application Programming Interface.
2) API is a software intermediary that allows two application to communicate with each other.
3) API is like a service through which we can request for the data.
4) Ex:   Each time you use an app like Facebook, send an instance message, or check the weather on your phone, you are using an API.

5) If we want to fetch data from API then we use requests module
   in requests module, requests() method is used to fetch data from API

